# Local Docker — ZERO database contact (NO EXCEPTIONS)

**This rule has no exceptions. Not for tests. Not for migrations. Not for debugging.**

Local stack = `docker-compose.yml`. Dev data = **MySQL `xflickr`** + **MongoDB `xflickr`**.

## Agents MUST NOT

Use `docker compose` (without `-f docker-compose.test.yml`) for anything that reads/writes databases:

- `docker compose exec app php artisan …` (almost all artisan commands)
- `docker compose exec mysql …`
- `docker compose exec mongodb …`
- `php artisan test`, `migrate`, `migrate:fresh`, `db:seed`, `db:wipe`, `tinker`
- `mongosh`, `mysql`, Redis flush on dev

**Reason:** `RefreshDatabase` wiped dev MySQL. MongoDB holds app credentials separately. Both are user data.

`docker compose exec` bypasses entrypoint guards.

## Agents MAY ONLY (local stack)

- `docker compose up|down|build|restart|logs|ps|pull`
- `docker compose exec app composer install`
- `docker compose exec app npm ci` / `npm run build`

## Database work — test stack ONLY

```bash
composer test:docker
./scripts/test-docker.sh
docker compose -f docker-compose.test.yml run --rm test php artisan test
```

## User-explicit maintenance only

Run **only** if the user explicitly requests it by name:

- `./scripts/reset-local-mongodb.sh`

Never improvise DB resets or migrations on local stack.

See [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md) and [`ai/skills/xflickr-docker-testing/SKILL.md`](../../ai/skills/xflickr-docker-testing/SKILL.md).
